    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-28T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-28T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 28, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 559. Re Kashmir. <gloss
                        target="#t_BritEmb1">Brit Emb</gloss> has referred <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> interest publication Devers plan (re <gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                        >Delga</gloss> 802) and reported word from Fowler that <gloss
                        target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> Del wld be satisfied if Graham at early mtg
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> wld discuss plan. <gloss
                        target="#t_BritEmb1">Brit Emb</gloss> has also mentioned that according info
                    recd from Paris Sir B N Ran has said he interested in knowing why Graham
                    abandoned a plan which <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> had all but accepted
                    and that he might raise question in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> (which wld
                    have effect opening up discussion Devers plan).</p>
                <p>As pointed out <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 502 and <gloss
                        target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 553 Dept has considered it undesirable
                    stimulate open discussion Devers plan at such early date. Dept interested <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>’s views re motives <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> and India in seeking bring plan into open.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
